<p>At <a
href="https://events.linuxfoundation.org/open-source-summit-europe/">Open
Source Summit Europe</a>, LWN's Jonathan Corbet presented "<a
href="https://osseu2025.sched.com/event/25Vq3">Three Decades in
Kernelland</a>"; the talk provides a look at how the kernel got to
where it is, what makes it successful, and what may be coming
next. The <a
href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LS2LGMRzE1I">video of the
talk</a> is now online for LWN readers who would like to check it
out.</p>

